     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>TO THE READER.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>REade if you will: And if you will not chuse,</l>
      <l>My booke (Sir) shall be read though you refuse:</l>
      <l>But if you doe, I pray commend my wit:</l>
      <l>For by my faith 't is first that ere I writ.</l>
      <l>Who reades and not commends, it is a rule</l>
      <l>To hold him very wise, or very foole.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>But whosoere commends, and doth not reede,</l>
      <l>What ere the other is, he's a foole indeede:</l>
      <l>But who doth neither reade nor yet commend,</l>
      <l>God speed him well, his labour's at an end.</l>
      <l>But reade, or praise, or not, or how it pas,</l>
      <l>I rest your honest, carelesse friend,</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>Will. Bas.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
